 <purpose>This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the definition of  assembly_feature_relationships and provides general representations for relationships between
component parts within an assembly model. The distinction between assembly, subassembly and component part is context dependent.
 
 </purpose>

<inscope>
 	  <li>the association of shape aspect relationship with its representation relationship;</li>
	  <li>the association of instanced assembly feature relationship with its representation relationship;</li>
	  <li>positioned assembly_feature_relationshipes, defined in three-dimensional model space;</li>  
	  <li>the representation of the fixed constituent which plays the anchor role in the assembly model;</li>
	  <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="contextual_shape_positioning:1_scope">Contextual shape positioning</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1027;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="foundation_representation:1_scope">Foundation representation</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1006;</li>
